  "prompt": "I'm using Tinder since last week. I press green heart to almost every profile, but didn't get even a single response. Why?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you're not getting matches on Tinder despite pressing the green heart (liking) on many profiles. Here are some common factors to consider:\n\n### 1. **Your Profile Needs Improvement**\n   - **Photos**: Are your photos clear, high-quality, and showcase your personality? Avoid group photos, blurry images, or selfies in the bathroom.\n   - **Bio**: Do you have a thoughtful bio that gives potential matches an idea of who you are? A blank or generic bio might not stand out.\n   - **Vibe**: Does your profile convey positivity and approachability? Profiles that seem negative or boastful can be off-putting.\n\n### 2. **Swipe Strategy**\n   - If you're swiping right (liking) on every profile, Tinder's algorithm might flag your account as spam or less genuine. It\u2019s better to be selective and only swipe right on profiles you\u2019re genuinely interested in.\n   - Over-swiping can also lower your Elo score (Tinder's internal ranking system), which makes your profile less visible to others.\n\n### 3. **Timing and Activity**\n   - Are you active at the right times? If you\u2019re swiping when fewer people are online, you might not get immediate responses.\n   - Be patient\u2014matches can take time, especially if you\u2019re new to the app.\n\n### 4. **Your Preferences and Location**\n   - If you\u2019re in a less populated area or have very specific preferences (e.g., age range, distance), it might limit your potential matches.\n   - Consider broadening your preferences slightly to increase your chances.\n\n### 5. **Account Issues**\n   - Ensure your account is set up correctly and is not shadowbanned (meaning your profile isn\u2019t visible to others). Signs of a shadowban include no matches or messages despite active use.\n\n### 6. **Competition**\n   - On apps like Tinder, competition can be high. Stand out by improving your profile and being authentic.\n\n### 7. **Algorithm Learning**\n   - Since you\u2019re new, the algorithm might still be learning your preferences. It can take a little time for it to show your profile to the right people.\n\n### Tips to Improve Your Chances:\n   - Add more engaging photos (e.g., hobbies, travel, smiling).\n   - Write a unique and fun bio that reflects your personality.\n   - Swipe selectively and thoughtfully.\n   - Use Super Likes sparingly to show genuine interest in someone.\n   - Consider Tinder Gold to see who liked you and increase your visibility.\n\nGive it some time and work on optimizing your profile. If you\u2019re still not getting matches after a while, you might want to try other dating apps or platforms to see if they suit you better. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
